BMIasConfounder

Quynh Tran

July 24, 2014

This is to check if BMI is a confouding factor between disease and gene expressions.

The counts tables were generated previously using HTseq.sh shell script and merge.command on Hera. It removes the outlier data point from the analysis, which was patient 29. This script requires a transcript counts table. There is also a sample mapping file called patient_sample_mapping.csv which links the diagnosis the the samples. This file was most recently processed on Tue Sep 9 15:40:06 2014.

This step gets the protein coding genes only.
